# Git Workflow

## Branch Strategy

```
master          Production-ready code
  ↑
feature/*       Feature development  (e.g. feature/tickets-module)
bugfix/*        Bug fixes            (e.g. bugfix/auth-token-expiry)
hotfix/*        Emergency fixes      (e.g. hotfix/sql-injection)
cursor/*        AI agent branches    (e.g. cursor/123-add-comments)
```

- Cloud/AI agents must always work on a `cursor/<ticket>-<summary>` branch
- Never push directly to `master`
- Open a PR for every change — no direct commits to main branches

## Commit Message Format (Conventional Commits)

```
<type>(<scope>): <short description>

feat(tickets): add priority filter to list endpoint
fix(auth): handle expired JWT gracefully
docs: update API endpoint reference
chore: add husky pre-commit hooks
refactor(users): extract password hashing to util
test(tickets): add integration tests for status transitions
```

**Types:** `feat` · `fix` · `docs` · `style` · `refactor` · `test` · `chore` · `perf`

**Rules:**
- Lowercase, imperative mood ("add" not "added")
- Scope is the module name: `auth`, `users`, `tickets`, `comments`, `attachments`
- Never use `--no-verify` to skip hooks

## Husky Hooks (already configured)

- **pre-commit:** lint-staged runs ESLint + Prettier on staged files
- Hooks cannot be bypassed — fix lint errors before committing

## Versioning

Use Semantic Versioning (SemVer):
- Format: `v{MAJOR}.{MINOR}.{PATCH}`
- Tag on every production release: `git tag v1.2.3`

## Recent Branch History

- `master` — primary branch
- `auth_setup` — auth feature branch (merged)
- `backend_setup` — backend scaffolding (merged)
